Doing some sit-ups with my BaseBench Pro by @baseblocks! 

1-Legs and arms straight, keep your ribs tucked in at all time. Do not take a break between reps.

2-Squeeze the foam with your legs, and avoid taking a break between reps when you go down.

Finally, always remember to keep the maximum muscular contraction during the peak of your movement. 

Link in my bio to check out my equipment!

node.text: I always liked to go back to the basement of my parents’ house where I grew up because it’s like a time capsule of my life. It always brings back good souvenirs. The old map who made me want to travel the world, the old fight posters of my early career, my old bedroom where all my karate certificates are now plus all the pictures and newspapers articles... I think it’s very important to always remember where you came from!
